snippet.textDisplay: To all the people that are suffering from depression. Isolating. Choosing to always be alone, but deep down slowly suffering from the loneliness. To have the desire to find love, but don’t know how to complete the process....So instead, we stay in our head beating ourselves up over it & allowing the depression to keep recapturing us.This song is for you. This is for ME. Let’s stop letting depression ambush us. Let’s start loving ourselves , let’s start mating with our own souls so that we may then be well enough to find our soul mate. ❤️😘

snippet.textDisplay: I can NOT explain how much this song resonates with me. Sam you are an amazing human. Queer or not you're such a special human. I hope one day I can thank you in person for this song. You've woken up something so special in me knowing I can still dream about love!! One day it will happen for both of us. Maybe WE will even get married & have a large zoo family one day!! Dreams can come TRU!!! Being a young 40ish queer person I have looked for love my entire life. I thought I found it a couple times, but boy was I wrong. This song gives me hope. This song gets me out of bed when I'm sad. This song gives me faith that they might be out there still.

snippet.textDisplay:
What have the Sam said about the song?
In an interview with Zane Lowe for Apple Music Sam Smith said that the song was inspired when they were walking down the beach boulevard in the Los Angeles Venice neighbourhood; “ … everyone was happy because everyone’s happy on that road. Just partners everywhere, kissing, and families … it’s about feeling alone and feeling like you’re on the outside watching everyone else … ” . Masterpiece
